Notes for newbies & first timers
1.) Read the entire order processing TWICE before asking questions to Brad and his team
2.) Buy a little more than the quoted price to account for transfer fees (min $100 extra). For the $5000 (standard) which costs $750, buy $850 worth of BTC. The price they quote you at is the price you pay regardless of BTC goes up/down
3.) When sending the BTC to the wallet address and calculate a fee that will transfer quickly usually ~30 min. (I didn’t do this and it took 13+ hrs to confirm the transaction. You will end up having to send them an email and your order could potentially get cancelled)
4.) I recommend purchasing the overnight or the fastest shipping available to you.
5.) Like it’s been stated, do NOT deposit or make purchases in excess of $10,000. Person to person transactions should be okay (buying a used car from a person) but depositing/purchasing anything that has the potential to leave a paper trail (banks, stores, etc) is obviously stupid.
